## babylon azure storage container delete
Add the following key in your `config/deploy.yml` file 
```yaml
# Storage account name
storage_account_name: "..."
```
Containers status can be checked with the following ``az cli`` command
```bash
az storage container list --account-name "..." --output table
```

# Commands
```bash
babylon azure storage container delete test-container
```
Should ask for confirmation and delete the container
```bash
babylon azure storage container delete test-container -f
```
Should delete without asking for confirmation
Deleting nonexistent containers should display an explicit error